Hello.

I've been wondering whether the json created from an xml file should be overwriting the reoccurring structures I might have in a file.

Example
```
<dataset>
  <object>
    <id>1</id>
    <name>foo</name>
  </object>
  <object>
    <id>2</id>
    <name>bar</name>
  </object>
</dataset>
```
the created json looks like this:
```
{
  "object" : {
    "id" : 2,
    "name" : "bar"
  }
}
```

Shouldn't the json look more like this:
```
{
  "dataset" : {
    "object": [{
        "id": 1,
        "name": "foo"
      },
      {
        "id": 2,
        "name": "bar"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

I'm using the fscrawler 2.4 release
